docs.lead_paragraph: "I must tell you," said a young woman at luncheon a few days ago, "how I added to the gayety of Europe when I was over last season. At Florence I bought, as everybody does, a bust of Dante, done in wonderfully clear and beautiful marble. It cost $1, but looked $20 at least, and was consequently precious as a bargain, besides being interesting as a possession.
